<p>The goal is to write a C program to convert a floating point number into its IEEE 754 single precision representation, and vice versa. It should take as input either a floating point number or an hexadecimal number, and output the corresponding hexadecimal IEEE 754 single precision representation or the corresponding base-10 floating point value. Examples of calls are given below: </p>  <blockquote>   <p>convert.exe 0Xabcd1231.81824e-32 &lt;-> 0xABCD123<br>   convert.exe 2.83234e-20.0283234 &lt;-> 0x3CE8067AY    The inputs are passed as arguments using the terminal.</p> </blockquote>